Name: Two Golden Earrings of King Ramesses the Eleventh
Description: This pair of gold earrings, bearing the name of King Ramesses the Eleventh, was found on a female mummy. They are formed of convex disks grooved along the edge and decorated with five uraei, or royal cobras, on the outer face. The three snakes in the middle bear a sun disk while the two outer ones wear the Atef crown. Five other snakes are attached to the sheet of gold, which is welded to the lower part of the disk and decorated with an image of the winged sun disk. The five cobras rest on a small bar from which hang seven pendants.
